This square has been transformed into a park, which is nice. There are games for little ones. The environment is rather calm so it's perfect for a break. On the other hand, I find that the greenery is not present enough.

Small neighborhood square set back from two major automobile routes so quite quiet. Individual benches, quite pleasant to take a break in the shade. Well-maintained children's play area and a book drop-off box available to the public as well as waste containers at the side exit of the square.
Small but beautiful and quiet garden

Small, cozy green area in the shape of a triangle with benches and individual seats, children's playground. Not far from Gare Montparnasse (less than a 5-minute walk from the east exit), surrounded by restaurants and small shops, including a supermarket (Monoprix). I always like to come here for a break and a snack before continuing my journey from Gare Montparnasse, if time and weather permits!

A small park near the Montparnasse station, a play area for the grandchildren, a few benches and chairs to sit on. The park is shaded and surrounded by tall buildings. Ideal for a short lunch break. Set back from the main roads around the station.
Square with games for children, my niece had a lot of fun with the other children. And all around the little benches.
Pretty, quiet park a stone's throw from Gare Montparnasse

Square ideally designed for loners and single parents thanks to these single-seater benches. #UnconnectingPeople. If you want more conviviality, I recommend the Atlantic Garden, a 3-minute walk from it.
I got there, being early to go to the theater. Very friendly space with its play area for children. To be preserved in the face of real estate sharks...

Away from the noise, lots of shade, a very pleasant little square for a lunch break.
